        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 5 at 4:08PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 408 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Alamosa, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Alamosa, San Luis Valley Airport and Alamosa East.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
